content:
Einstein Bots includes two types of data: event data and intent data. Intent data is discussed in Intent Management.

Hierarchy of Bot Event Data:

The bot stores different types of data at the Bot Name level versus the Bot Version level.

At the Bot Name level, available data includes:
- Bot Name
- Bot API Name
- Bot Description
- Channel Association
- Entities
- Local Intents & Utterances
- Intent Sets

At the Bot Version level, different data is stored, including:
- Bot Language
- Bot Response Delay
- Log Conversations
- Bot User
- Dialogs
- Variables

Reporting on Bot Event Data:

Bot event data can be built into reports by creating custom report types on the Conversation Definition object.
The entities that you can use inside report types are in the Bot Data Reference Guide.

Due to high volume, bot event and session data are only stored for 7 days. You can download this data or copy it to another object for longer storage.

A list of bot objects, events, and fields is provided in the Bot Data Reference Guide.
Bot event data deletion can have unintended ramifications on the data model. To back out a dialog intent set from a bot, remove the intent set from the dialog and then delete the dialog.
Turn off the Log Conversation Data setting if you have concerns about capturing personal identifying information (PII) of your customers.
